Syntax: refuel <light> <fuel> {"held" | "room"}

This command is used to refuel lamps of all things.  The <light> must
be extinguished before refueling may begin.  The <light> must be
held, in your inventory or in the room, and the <fuel> must be in your
inventory or held.

The "held" and "room" argument may be used to limit your search for <light>
to your inventory/equipment or the room you are in respectively.

See Also : LIGHT, EXTINGUISH
Related Topics: OBJECT MANIPULATION
